						<summary>

						<p>This is a badly damaged inscription. It is dated in Śaka 1194, Āṅgirasa, Mārgaḻi (1272-73 A.D.) and seems to record a grant of 15 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land to god Śokkapperumāḷ for some offerings. Mention is made of an illegal occupation of a land after removing the boundary stone and of one Tiruvanantāḻvāṉ-Bhaṭṭaṉ who was apparently the aggrieved person but was able to produce documents proving his ownership rights. The details are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
